gcc main.c -o main
gcc process1.c -o process1
gcc process2.c -o process2
gcc process3.c -o process3


Each time you want a process to update the balance, run this: 
./main 1 OR ./main 2 OR ./main 3

to remove a shared memory that already exist
ipcrm -m <shmid>

start the program with running
make

then run
./initializer

then processes
./process1
./process2
./process3
